[assistant]   "summary": "mchange-commons-java 0.6.0 enforces JNDI JavaBean/reference security whitelists; tests that exercise JavaBeanReferenceMaker or JavaBeanObjectFactory will fail until the test bean class is explicitly whitelisted.",
[assistant]   "deterministic_setup": [],
[assistant]   "agent_guidance": "For tests that create or resolve JNDI References for JavaBeans, set system property `com.mchange.v2.naming.referenceableJavaBeanClassWhitelist` to the exact fully qualified test bean class name before calling `JavaBeanReferenceMaker.createReference(...)` or `JavaBeanObjectFactory.getObjectInstance(...)`, and restore/clear it afterward. If using `ReferenceableUtils.referenceToObject(...)` overloads without an explicit allowed factory set, also set `com.mchange.v2.naming.objectFactoryWhitelist` to the exact test ObjectFactory class name; prefer explicit allow sets when possible. Do not use `*` unless the test is deliberately covering the unsafe opt-out behavior.",
[assistant]   "risks": [
[assistant]     "The whitelist properties are global system properties; leaking them across tests can hide failures or produce intersection behavior if another config source also sets a whitelist.",
[assistant]     "Generated inner test classes used as whitelisted JavaBeans or ObjectFactories still need normal reachability coverage in native-image tests."
[assistant]   ]
[assistant] }
