ed.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For tests that create or resolve JNDI References for JavaBeans, set system property `com.mchange.v2.naming.referenceableJavaBeanClassWhitelist` to the exact fully qualified test bean class name before calling `JavaBeanReferenceMaker.createReference(...)` or `JavaBeanObjectFactory.getObjectInstance(...)`, and restore/clear it afterward. If using `ReferenceableUtils.referenceToObject(...)` overloads without an explicit allowed factory set, also set `com.mchange.v2.naming.objectFactoryWhitelist` to the exact test ObjectFactory class name; prefer explicit allow sets when possible. Do not use `*` unless the test is deliberately covering the unsafe opt-out behavior.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The whitelist properties are global system properties; leaking them across tests can hide failures or produce intersection behavior if another config source also sets a whitelist.\",\n    \"Generated inner test classes used as whitelisted JavaBeans or ObjectFactories still need normal reachability coverage in native-image tests.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0788b5a9ea694e4d016a3fdb0e86248195a69fa0b898128088\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 494, "output": 803, "cacheRead": 25088, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 26385, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782569732714, "responseId": "resp_0788b5a9ea694e4d016a3fdb052db08195b4bb3c0f3b16eae2"}, "toolResults": []}
